          about2: `Natural disasters have a wide array of effects on the environment and the species that inhabit it. Hurricanes, wildfires, floods, and tsunamis can cause devastation for both wildlife and people alike.`,
          about3: `Animals and plants can be directly affected by the force of a natural disaster, as well as the destruction of their habitats. Wildfires can cause direct physical harm to animals, as well as wiping out entire species in a single event. Floods can wash away habitats, leaving animals with nowhere to go. Hurricanes can also cause destruction, uprooting trees and flooding habitats with salt water, destroying the delicate balance of the ecosystem. Tsunamis can cause even more destruction than hurricanes, flooding entire coastlines and decimating animal populations. The destruction of coral reef ecosystems can have long-term consequences for species that depend on those habitats for food, shelter, and breeding.`,
